
List as abstract data type

- Store a given number of elements of
  a given data-type
- Write/modify element of a position
- Read element at a position

Arrays

int a[10];
a[i] = 2
print a[i];

- empty list has size 0
- insert -|
- remove -| -- shift
- count
- Read/modify element at a
  position
- specify data-type

int a[maxsize];
int end=-1;
insert(2);

when array is full, create
new larger array of double size,
copy elements from previous array
into the new array.
free the memory for the previous
array.

problem : Not dynamic

1. Access - Read/write element at an index - Constant time - O(1)
2. Insert - shift - O(n)
3. Remove - O(n)
4. Add - O(n)
